column5: hey guys, anyone know how thick the ice is on cooks bay, Im itching to get out there but dont want to drive up from toronto if the ice is not ready, so if anyone knows what the current thickness is that would be great. if its not thick enough for my liking i guess i will be back in Orangville at Island lake again this weekend.
Off the end of gillford rd has 5-6 inches conservativly
I wonder how many of these threads we'll have this year.   This has gotta be what?  #4 or #5?  lol
just look at the bright side bill....soft water is a commin sooooooooner!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
I wanna get out for whities and lakers!  I don't mind the break at all
I went out from Gilford today. It was a solid 5-6 inches.
any sleds/ quads out there? im thinking of giving it a shot over the weekend

out of gilford yesterday about 3/4 of the ice had zero snow and was very slick. chains, airing down to 1 psi, or studs would be a good idea for the quads.  6" of solid black ice out there means it's a-ok for the machines.
Right on thanks... hopefull we get some snow overnight... should be busy out there on the weekend
YA,HOW MANY   WILL PARK ON THE ICE?
Baaaaaa, baaaaaa , black sheep.  Park really close to the other guy too, hate to see just one go down.
Hahahahaha, apparantely the first doofus went through all by himself, how unfortunate, not inviting any friends.
Lets hope that the temps this week won't ruin it for us!!
